  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While white-collar crime involving a breach of trust is serious, the relatively low amount of $25,000 and the lack of a criminal history call for a sentence that focuses on restitution and deterrence rather than excessive imprisonment. A six-month term of incarceration is appropriate to address the gravity of the breach of fiduciary duty.",
